Checking state of std::ifstream object

1)	if (!ifs.is_open())

   	 This means that the file stream object (ifs) was attempted to be opened with a file, 
		but the operation failed. 
	This can happen due to various reasons such as 
	- file not found, 
	- lack of permissions, or 
	- other file system issues.

2) 	if (!ifs)
	
	This checks if the stream is in a failed state, 
		- which includes scenarios beyond just file open failure, 
		- such as reading or writing errors during operations.
